a district in Barcelona province.","Spanish: habitational name from any of the places called Valles, from the plural of <i>valle</i> ‘valley’."],"variants":[{"name":"Baltazar","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Jose, Juan, Pedro, Guadalupe, Jesus, Luis, Gustavo, Jorge, Manuel, Miguel, Roberto, Francisco.  Portuguese Godofredo, Joao, Joaquim, Wenceslao.  Italian Antonio, Romeo, Lorenzo, Ciro, Carmela, Cecilio, Clemente, Clementina, Fausto, Flavio, Leonardo, Marco.","Spanish, Portuguese, Catalan, and German; Hungarian and Slovak (<b>Baltazár</b>): from the Biblical personal names <i>Balthazar</i> and <i>Belshazzar</i>, which were originally distinct but by medieval times had come to be regarded as variants of a single name. The first is from Aramaic <i>Balshatzar</i>, Babylonian <i>Baal tas-assar</i> ‘may Baal preserve his life’, the second from Babylonian <i>Baal shar-uzzur</i> ‘may Baal protect the king’. The latter was borne by the Chaldean king for whom the Hebrew prophet Daniel interpreted the writing on the wall (Daniel 5). The main reason for the popularity of <i>Balthazar</i> as a personal name in medieval Europe was that, according to legend, it was the name of one of the three Magi from the East who attended Christ's birth. His supposed relics were venerated at first in Milan, but after 1164 in Cologne. This surname is most common in Mexico.","Altered form of Italian   Baldassarre   or one of its variants or cognates."]}]},{"name":"Thomas","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament name, borne by one of Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Thomas Balles was born in 1537, in Suffolk, England, United Kingdom as the son of Mr BALIE Balles and Mrs Balie Balles. He had at least 3 sons and 1 daughter with Joan Spalding."},"et":{"1537–":"1537–Surnud","1537–Male":"1537–Surnud","1541–Female":"1541–Surnud","1563–Male":"1563–Surnud","1565–1620":"1565–1620","1565–Female":"1565–Surnud","1518–Male":"1518–Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1565":"1565","1620":"1620","1563":"1563","ABT 1563":"umbes 1563","1541":"1541","about 1565":"umbes 1565","1518":"1518","1537":"1537","Framlingham, Suffolk, England":"Framlingham, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Framingham, Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1537–":"1537–Kuollut","1537–Male":"1537–Kuollut","1541–Female":"1541–Kuollut","1563–Male":"1563–Kuollut","1565–1620":"1565–1620","1565–Female":"1565–Kuollut","1518–Male":"1518–Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1565":"1565","1620":"1620","1563":"1563","ABT 1563":"noin 1563","1541":"1541","about 1565":"noin 1565","1518":"1518","1537":"1537","Framlingham, Suffolk, England":"Framlingham, Suffolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Framingham, Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1537–":"1537–Décédé","1537–Male":"1537–Décédé","1541–Female":"1541–Décédée","1563–Male":"1563–Décédé","1565–1620":"1565–1620","1565–Female":"1565–Décédée","1518–Male":"1518–Décédé","–Female":"Décédée","1565":"1565","1620":"1620","1563":"1563","ABT 1563":"environ 1563","1541":"1541","about 1565":"environ 1565","1518":"1518","1537":"1537","Framlingham, Suffolk, England":"Framlingham, Suffolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Framingham, Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Thomas Balles est né en 1537, à Suffolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, fils de Mr BALIE Balles et Mrs Balie Balles. Il a eu au moins 3 fils et 1 fille avec Joan Spalding."},"de":{"1537–":"1537–Verstorben","1537–Male":"1537–Verstorben","1541–Female":"1541–Verstorben","1563–Male":"1563–Verstorb